<br>
The Golden Dragon was infact an insturment of Bia, perhaps akin to some terrible guard.  Having sensed  the Presence of Hypnos  (as well as his fear of being visible), the dragon was now ready to strike.<br>
<br>
Bia had by now located the hidden figure herself.  Her eyes too showed a fierce glow like a sun about to explode.  Yet she stroked the dragon and tried to calm it.<br>
In an effort to resolve this before it went further she communicated telepathically to Hypnos: <br>
<br>
&quot;I know not why hiding is preferable to being visible.  For the latter could only assure me and all here that your intentions are honourable.  The former, however, is uncertain and unsafe in my presence. Moreover, I assure you you have not known the like of me, nor I counsel you, should you wish this to go further,&quot; she looked towards Hypnos now, her eyes ablaze of fiery gold, adding, &quot;I must dispatch my duties in this regard.  For I am Goddess Bia, Goddess of Force and Power, Warrior and Guardian of Zeus. You may know I take my duties in all seriousness.  Either you must explain why you hide so, or I must act in my duties.  I prefer an adequate explanation, as this is a feast of happiness and I wish it to remain so.  But, I charge you now Hypnos, explain to me why, or become visible. Or I must act. These are your choices .&quot;  <br>
<br>
Her words were stern and authoritative, there was no malcontent in her, merely he obligation to those here present in her duty to Zeus and Hera.  Her glowing eyes, like two fierce fireballs, told Hypnos she was serious and his presence &quot;being invisible&quot; was an error he had power to correct............<br>
<br>
 <p>~ ~ Bia  Goddess of Force and Power: Warrior and Guardian of Zeus ~ ~

