<br>
As he moved along the tiled flooring,a dark shadow enveloped him and followed him. His greyen orbs scanning over the rather large gathering of Gods.<br>
<br>
As he moved over to the tables where food and drink were waiting,it appeared as though he were floating. He took up a chalice of fine wine,and drank.<br>
<br>
He wasn't here for any social reason,only curious about what brings the gods to gather for a feast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessbia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Bia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.amazon.com/images/P/1560252154.01.LZZZZZZZ.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/21/02 7:05:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.phoenixarises.com/wof/royo6.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Bia looked at Hypnos, her eyes showing she had calmed a little, but also indicating to him that he was  on infirm ground with her.  <br>
<br>
&quot;He wishes to be at peace while invisible,&quot; she questioned herself,&quot; Me thinks if he truely wished to conduct private business, this is not the place or time to do so.  Moreover, getting &quot;mad&quot; with Bia would indeed be a mistake, for Bia (like her sister and brothers) were without equal, this is why Zeus had appointed them his Guardians.<br>
<br>
The Dragon on Bia's shoulder was still growing, albeit at a slower rate than before.  It too had calmed slightly, but was still carefully watching Hypnos, ready to pounce at the least indication.  It's eyes glowed a deeper more menacing fury of red fire and instead of smoke, licks of flame exuded from it's mouth and nostrils.<br>
<br>
Bia herself was also transforming,  Her huge stature becoming ever greater, the gold of her raiment assuming a darker colour and the fireballs which were eyes assuming a greater intensity.  She was indeed beginning to show herself the very Personification of Force and Power, which indeed she was.  However, this was a place to beware.  To remember the real purpose of this gathering of the gods and therefore to restrain her instinctive nature.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well, Hypnos,&quot; she said at length,&quot;I will allow you a few moments to get your answer from Athena.  But no more than a few moments. &quot; She arched an eyebrow to emphasise that she was indeed serious. &quot;But I also caution you this,&quot; she continued,&quot; be you not invisible in my presence again.  For I shall not shrink from taking that as proof of your insincerety.  If, however, you do not receive an answer from Athena presently,  I advise you to assume that she agrees this is not a place for such dalliances, nor for your cloaked demeener.  Rather, it is better, for your own answers, to be visible and to win respect again (though how you lost it I know not) by being clear therefore.&quot;<br>
<br>
With this Bia gave Hypnos a look of fierce warning.  Her words were wise, if he understood them he would shortly make his presence known to all, for this was indeed the only possible way in which he could win their respect and trust.  How could he not know that by being devious as he was, he was incurring his own dishonour among them.  For indeed, all present were Gods.  All were capable of &quot;knowing&quot; as she knew.  She hoped, for his sake, he understood the wisdom of this. For if not, and if he did not respect her counsel in this matter, it would not, it could not, pass without notice or account being payed.......<br>
<br>
She moved a little way off from where he stood.  Her transformation unabated.  The Dragon now stood beside her it's menacing ferocity a clear signal that it was alert and prepared to do what might be necessary.  As indeed was Bia.  But she would allow Hypnos a curtesy he was not showing all else here.  She would restrain herself for a few moments as she had promised.................<br>
<br>
She noted the darkness and the being which emmerged from it.  She gave a slow nod of acknowledgement and returned to what occupied her, though also observing the new visitor amongst them.............. <p>~ ~ Bia  Goddess of Force and Power: Warrior and Guardian of Zeus ~ ~

