<br>
'So you have seen the tension in Athena huh? Yeah she has a grudge against me, anyways what happened is past and done. I don't know why she is still mad' he smirks, 'she's still a virgin.'<br>
<br>
Poseidon waves over a nearby cup-bearer who hands him a goblet and Poseidon takes it happily. 'Thank you' he addresses the youthful man. The drink is emptied quickly as it is thrown down the sea god's throat. He places the goblet on the table and looks again at that marvelous dress of Hecate. 'You know I must say you do look stunning Hecate.'<br>
<br>
He licks his lips and answers Hecates question about his wife. 'Yes you are right, Amphitrite would not be here because she is vacationing with her father. I've no idea when she'll return but she should be back by the time I return from meeting the Ethiopians.'<br>
<br>
'Have you taken a bite to eat or are you content?' he asks Hecate. 'I know I am starving and there is plenty to go around.' At his behest one of Hephaestus' magical tables rolls in carrying a tray of prepared food up to the table. Poseidon takes the dishes of the tray and sets them on the table. The dishes click on the hardness of the table and the scent of the food rises into his nostrils.<br>
<br>
