<br>
She first walked to Gaia respectivly and greeted her, talking for a few to THE Earth goddess, she then greeted the others, spyng her brother Poseidon in the corner with Hecate, she walked over and interupted. &quot;It has been a many moon since I have seen you dear brother of mine.&quot;  She bent over and placed a kiss upon his cheek then embraced him in a strong hug.  She then turned to Hecate and nodded to her. &quot;Hello dear.&quot; She then turned back to her brother, winiked and headed off. <br>
<br>
Noticing Eris, she smiled and nodded to the little trouble maker. Not many was fond of the Goddess of Discord, but Demeter knew that Olympus as well as the Earth would be lost and out of control without her. She then spotted her sister Hera and walked over to her. A brighter smile on her face. &quot;Dearest of my sisters, Queen of the Gods...&quot; She embraced her sister in a long hug, patting her back.  &quot; I havent been in your presence in a long long time. How goes it? Well I hope.&quot;  She looked over and noticed that Zeus was busy with Athena, she would greet her brother later. She then waved to the Furies and anyone else she missed. <p>:*: Goddess Demeter, Goddess of the Harvest. Controller of the seasons and weather. :*:</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessgaiax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Gaiax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/22/02 5:35:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> La da da (couldnt think of a title)</span><hr size=1> First, Gaia had not spoken to Poseidon for the Athena indcident, and of course she knew that the Sea god and Hekate had...a thing.<br>
<br>
Gaia bowed her head in respect to Lord Zeus before turning to her daughters, The Furies.<br>
<br>
&quot;My dear daughters, you bring me any honour and pride I have, how are my children fairing this day?&quot;<br>
<br>
She nodded in greeting to any others, and spoke a few words with Demeter, a Newer Generation Nature Goddess. Of course, after all this she returned her attention to her Daughters, The Furies.<br>
