&quot;Hello, Mother.&quot; ::he said as he nodded to her, then went to greet his father who was conversing with Athena. A smile on his lips.:: &quot;Hello Father, A6thena..How are the both of you? Havent seen you both in a dog's day.&quot;   :::He spoke with them briefly, and spotted Poseidon and Hecate talking in the corner...yea, that wasn't too obvious, knowing his Uncles reputation was almost as bad as his own. He walked to them, winking first to Hecate, then patting his Uncle on his back.::  &quot;Well here's the guest of honor, not such the sociable host huh?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/23/02 9:34:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To be a host.</span><hr size=1> Before Hecate speaks a loud crash comes from across the hall. The sea god looks over and sees the male servant who dropped the dishes pick them up looking quite shaken. Eris seems to be responsible or more obviously likes what she sees as Poseidon espies her out giggling. <br>
<br>
Bia catches his eye of a sudden, that powerful goddess, as she seems to be concentrating on something, her mind away from the feast, Athena as well. This was happening for a little while and the god had a hunch as to what it may be. Hypnos! Sure Poseidon could sense him there, he was immortal and in the same hall. The god decides at that moment to leave him be, but at the same time another thought comes of personally escorting the unwanted guest out. However, he keeps to his place, but will not tolerate Hypnos if he even makes himself tangible.<br>
<br>
A shadow falls over him and as a soft body closes in on his Poseidon can tell immediately that it is his sister, former lover, Demeter by that sent of hers. The immortal god returns the kiss he recieves and smiles. &quot;Welcome Demeter! Do enjoy yourself and make well. All provisions needy of a feast are at your disposal. I'll join in the social events after a minute or two with Hecate here.&quot; He nods over in Hecates direction. The earth goddess walks off after a wink and Poseidon stares at her, the wonderful etrnally youthful body of hers only an immortal, a queen among immortals can possess.<br>
<br>
After Demeter leaves them alone once again Poseidon folds his hands under his chin and stares at Hecate while she speaks. &quot;Hungry for something else eh? I wonder what it is that you hunger for!&quot; Just then another guest comes over, the most hated God of all Olympus. Ares the war god who questions his lack of being a suitable host. Poseidon laughs it off and shakes Ares hand. &quot;Welcome Ares, excuse my not greeting you sooner, Hecate and I were here speaking for a minute. Though I do suppose it is time for me to entertain my guests as it seems I am needed.&quot;<br>
<br>
He rises and turns to Hecate. &quot;We can continue this later Hecate. I've got to greet my wonderfully thoughtful guests who have arrived and not been properly hosted.&quot; He winks at her in turn as Demeter had winked at him and leaves Ares and Hecate together at the table. Poseidon's plate almost finished of its food is still at the spot he sat at and is quickly cleared by youthful servants. The band is just finishing playing a tune when Poseidon tells them to play something more vibrant to uplift spirits. The chorus then starts singing the story of the Olympians triumph over the giants.<br>
<br>
The god walks away strutting in a Dionystic type revel manner and with an uplifted voice speaks to the crowd. &quot;The main course will soon be served everyone and do welcome our wonderful minstel's song of Olympian triumph.&quot; He claps for them as they play the song in its entirety cheering them on. <br>
<br>
Poseidon then heads over to Zeus and pats his huge arm. &quot;So bro what do you think of the festivities? I hope it's to your liking.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
